{{also|Elephant|éléphant|êléphant}} ==English==
===Etymology=== [[File:Elephant near ndutu.jpg|thumb|African bush elephant ({{taxfmt|Loxodonta africana|species}})]] [[File:AmersfoortZooYoungAsianElephant.jpg|thumb|Asian elephant ({{taxfmt|Elephas maximus|species}})]]
From {{inh|en|enm|elefant}}, {{m|enm|elefaunt}}, from {{der|en|fro|elefant}}, {{m|fro|elefan}}, {{m|fro|olifant}}, re-latinized in {{der|en|frm|-}} as {{m|frm|elephant}}, from {{der|en|la|elephantus}}, from {{der|en|grc|ἐλέφᾱς}} (gen. {{m|grc|ἐλέφαντος}}). Believed to be derived from an {{der|en|afa|-}} form such as {{der|en|ber-pro|*eḷu|t=elephant}} (compare {{cog|thv|êlu}}, {{cog|taq|alu}}) or {{der|en|egy|ꜣbw|t=elephant; ivory}}. More at {{m|en|ivory}}. Replaced {{cog|enm|olifant}} (from the aforementioned {{w|Old French}} form, from {{cog|VL.|*olifantus}}), which replaced {{cog|ang|elpend|t=elephant}}.
===Pronunciation=== * {{IPA|en|/ˈɛl.ɪ.fənt/|a=RP}} * {{IPA|en|/ˈɛl.ə.fənt/|a=GA}} * {{audio|en|En-us-elephant.ogg|a=GA|IPA=/ˈɛl.ə.fənt/}} * {{IPA|en|/el.e.fant/|a=Philippines}} * {{IPA|en|/ɛlɪˈfaɳʈ/|/ˈɛlɪfəɳʈ/|a=Indic}} * {{hyphenation|en|ele|phant}}
===Noun=== {{en-noun|~}}
# {{senseid|en|Q7378}} A large [[mammal]] of the family {{taxfmt|Elephantidae|family}} in the order [[Proboscidea]], having a [[trunk]], and native to [[Africa]] and [[Asia]]. # {{lb|en|in particular}} Any member of the subfamily [[Elephantinae]] not also of the genera {{taxfmt|Mammuthus|genus}} and ''Primelephas''. # {{lb|en|figurative}} Anything [[huge]] and [[ponderous]]. # {{lb|en|paper|printing}} {{synonym of|en|elephant paper}}. # {{lb|en|British|childish}} {{n-g|used when counting to add length, so that each count takes about one second}} #: {{ux|en|Let's play hide and seek. I'll count. One '''elephant''', two '''elephant''', three '''elephant'''...}} # {{lb|en|uncountable|obsolete}} [[ivory|Ivory]]. #* {{RQ:Dryden Aeneis|passage=He sent rich gifts of '''elephant''' and gold.}} # {{lb|en|xiangqi}} A [[xiangqi]] [[piece]] that is moved two points [[diagonally]], may not jump over intervening pieces and may not cross the river.
